  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nThis refers to @MariusVanDerWijden's repo: https://github.com/MariusVanDerWijden/go-ethereum/commit/af18ae1b488f05bd49ec7a6bcc40e525e35c9b19\r\n\r\n*Note: this is a similar but different issue to #24404.*\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nThe [v1.0.0-alpha.6 api specs](https://github.com/ethereum/execution-apis/blob/v1.0.0-alpha.6/src/engine/specification.md) decares that a `new_payload` response must have `latestValidHash == null` when `status == SYNCING`:\r\n\r\n> - {status: SYNCING, latestValidHash: null, validationError: null} if the payload extends the canonical chain and requisite data for its validation is missing\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nWhen syncing [`merge-devnet-4`](https://notes.ethereum.org/D5xK4XrmTb6MKGudf_hcrg?view) Lighthouse is giving me:\r\n\r\n```\r\nnew_payload: response does not conform to engine API spec: PayloadStatusV1 { status: Syncing, latest_valid_hash: Some(0xa28d8d73e087a01d09d8cb806f60863652f30b6b6dfa4e0157501ff07d422399), validation_error: None }\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt appears that Geth is sending a non-null `latestValidHash` with the SYNCING response.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nI found this whilst syncing [`merge-devnet-4`](https://notes.ethereum.org/D5xK4XrmTb6MKGudf_hcrg?view) with Lighthouse on the `unstable` branch and Geth on `merge-kiln`.\r\n\r\nIt synced for a while at first, so I'm not exactly sure how to reproduce it. Happy to look into it more if you need :)",
